The Nigerian currency appreciated against the Dollar at both Investors and Exporters (I&E) Foreign Exchange window and the official window on Monday.
The Naira appreciated 0.02 per cent to N306.95/$1 at the Central Bank official forex window, while the Investors and Exporters (I&E) FX window opened at N362.46, traded high at N363.50 and eventually closed at N362.55, representing 0.06% appreciation against last Fridayâ€™s position.
Investors exchanged a total of $112.88 million was transacted through the I&E window.
At the parallel and interbank market, the Naira closed flat at N360/USD and N306.95/USD respectively.